  "prompt": "What is the dress code for fresher girls in Capgemini?",
  "response": "The dress code for fresher girls at Capgemini, like in most professional IT companies, is typically business casual or formal. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n### **Business Casual** (Most Common):\n- **Tops:** Formal shirts, blouses, or modest tops (avoid sleeveless or low-cut tops).\n- **Bottoms:** Formal trousers, skirts (knee-length or longer), or tailored pants.\n- **Dresses:** Knee-length, modest dresses in solid colors or subtle patterns.\n- **Footwear:** Closed-toe shoes, flats, or low heels.\n- **Accessories:** Minimal and professional (avoid flashy or excessive jewelry).\n\n### **Formal Wear** (for client meetings or specific events):\n- **Blazers:** Pair with formal shirts and trousers or skirts.\n- **Formal suits:** Well-fitted pantsuits or skirt suits.\n- **Footwear:** Closed-toe formal shoes or heels.\n- **Neutral Colors:** Stick to muted or neutral tones like black, navy, gray, or white.\n\n### **What to Avoid**:\n\u5e74 Casual wear like jeans, t-shirts, or sneakers.\n\u5e74 Revealing or overly tight clothing.\n\u5e74 Heavy makeup or strong perfume.\n\u5e74 Flip-flops or open-toed sandals.\n\n### **Cultural Considerations**:\nCapgemini is a global company, so dressing modestly and professionally is always appreciated. If you\u2019re in India, traditional Indian wear like salwar suits or kurtis with formal pants may also be acceptable on non-client-facing days.\n\nIt\u2019s always a good idea to check with your team or HR for specific guidelines, as dress codes can vary slightly based on location, department, or client requirements.",
